." lattice-netcat(1) - POSIX-oriented netcat for lattice runtime
."
.Dd January 25, 2026
.Dt LATTICE-NETCAT 1
.Os "Lattice Runtime"
.Sh NAME
.Nm lattice-netcat
.Nd POSIX-oriented netcat implementation for lattice runtime
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Op Fl l
.Op Fl uU S
.Op Fl k
.Op Fl v
.Op Fl p Ar port
.Op Fl H Ar host
.Op Fl L Ar socket
.Op Fl t Ar seconds
.Op Fl w Ar seconds
.Op Fl e Ar command
.Op Fl o Ar file
.Op Fl i Ar file
.Op Fl N
.Op Fl -fifo Ns = Ns Ar file
.Op Fl -pid-file Ns = Ns Ar file
.Op Fl -lattice-log Ns = Ns Ar file
.Op Ar host
.Op Ar port
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
is a POSIX-oriented netcat implementation designed for lattice runtime
transport creation. It prefers system tools such as
.Xr nc 1 ,
.Xr socat 1 ,
and
.Xr openssl 1 ,
falling back to portable methods where possible.
.Pp
It supports TCP, UDP, Unix sockets, SSL/TLS, FIFO integration, and
zero-I/O scanning.
.Sh OPTIONS
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Fl l , Fl -listen
Listen for incoming connections.
.It Fl u , Fl -udp
Use UDP instead of TCP.
.It Fl U , Fl -unix
Use Unix domain socket mode.
.It Fl S , Fl -ssl
Enable SSL/TLS mode.
.It Fl L Ar socket , Fl -local-socket Ns = Ns Ar socket
Unix socket path (with
.Fl U ) .
.It Fl k , Fl -keep-open
Keep listening after client disconnects.
.It Fl v , Fl -verbose
Verbose output.
.It Fl p Ar port , Fl -port Ns = Ns Ar port
Port to connect or listen on.
.It Fl H Ar host , Fl -host Ns = Ns Ar host
Host to connect to (client mode).
.It Fl t Ar seconds , Fl -timeout Ns = Ns Ar seconds
Connection timeout (default: 30).
.It Fl w Ar seconds , Fl -wait Ns = Ns Ar seconds
Wait time for connection in scan mode.
.It Fl -udp-wait Ns = Ns Ar seconds
Wait for a UDP reply in client mode.
.It Fl z , Fl -zero
Zero-I/O scan mode.
.It Fl e Ar command , Fl -exec Ns = Ns Ar command
Execute a command when connected (requires socat for server mode).
.It Fl c Ar command , Fl -command Ns = Ns Ar command
Alias for
.Fl e .
.It Fl o Ar file , Fl -output Ns = Ns Ar file
Write output to file.
.It Fl i Ar file , Fl -input Ns = Ns Ar file
Read input from file.
.It Fl N , Fl -no-shutdown
Do not shutdown socket on EOF.
.It Fl -fifo Ns = Ns Ar file
Use a FIFO for I/O.
.It Fl -pid-file Ns = Ns Ar file
Write PID to file.
.It Fl -lattice-log Ns = Ns Ar file
Log file for lattice runtime.
.El
.Sh ENVIRONMENT
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Ev LATTICE_NETCAT_DEBUG
Enable shell tracing.
.It Ev LATTICE_SSL_CERT
SSL certificate file.
.It Ev LATTICE_SSL_KEY
SSL private key file.
.It Ev LATTICE_SSL_CA
SSL CA certificate file.
.El
.Sh EXAMPLES
.Bd -literal -offset indent
# TCP client
lattice-netcat example.com 80

# TCP server
lattice-netcat -l -p 8080

# UDP client
lattice-netcat -u example.com 53

# Unix socket server
lattice-netcat -U -l -L /tmp/test.sock

# SSL client
lattice-netcat -S example.com 443

# FIFO mode
lattice-netcat --fifo=/tmp/pipe.fifo
.Ed
.Sh EXIT STATUS
.Ex -std
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr nc 1 ,
.Xr socat 1 ,
.Xr openssl 1 ,
.Xr mkfifo 1
.Sh AUTHORS
.An "Lattice Runtime Team"
